---
// Page 11 — Terms and conditions (legacy URL preserved). Legal copy is lifted
// VERBATIM from the harvest (fairytails-image-archive/terms-and-conditions/):
// only three unambiguous artefacts were fixed (a stray editorial line above
// clause 12 removed; "ETIRE" -> "ENTIRE"; "Aquisition" -> "Acquisition"), plus
// owner-approved cross-reference corrections (2026-07-04): 18→20, 20's
// "19/22-24"→"18/21-23", 23's self-ref→22, 32's self-ref→31, and "take of"→
// "take any of" in clause 22.
// Do not "improve" the legal wording without the owner's say-so.
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import HillDivider from '../components/HillDivider.astro';
import { business } from '../data/business';

const stages = [
  {
    name: 'Acquisition',
    points: [
      'Learning new skill.',
      'Learning is slow and inaccurate.',
      'Reinforcement is not contingent on correct behaviour but general learning mood.',
    ],
  },
  {
    name: 'Fluency / Maintenance',
    points: [
      'New skill is accurate but slow in response.',
      'Use of accurate reinforcement contingent on behaviour.',
      'Exposure to different stimuli.',
    ],
  },
  {
    name: 'Generalisation',
    points: [
      'Retention of skill/behaviour over time.',
      'Use of delayed reinforcement with novel situations and practice.',
      'Can use and adapt new skill to different environments but slow.',
    ],
  },
  {
    name: 'Adaptation',
    points: [
      'Independent, developed and able to cope.',
      'Use of initiative to adapt to new situations without support.',
      'Able to adjust quickly in different environments.',
    ],
  },
];
---

<Base
  title="Terms and Conditions | The Fairy Tails K9 Centre"
  description="The Fairy Tails K9 Centre terms and conditions — our quality policy and the dog day care agreement that covers every dog in our care."
  path="/terms-and-conditions"
>
  <article data-page="terms">
    <header class="bg-moss-900 pb-16 pt-32 sm:pb-20 sm:pt-40">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
        <p class="eyebrow text-honey-300">The important bit</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-4xl font-bold leading-tight text-cream-50 sm:text-5xl">
          Terms and conditions
        </h1>
      </div>
    </header>
    <HillDivider class="text-moss-900" flip />

    <div class="post-body mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pb-20 pt-10 sm:pt-14">
      <h2>Our quality policy</h2>
      <p>
        At the Fairy Tails we are committed to the high quality of the service and it is at the
        centre of everything we do.
      </p>
      <p>
        Quality to us means the welfare and health of all animals in our care and the delivery of
        good service to our customers from first contact, throughout their stay, as until they go
        home.
      </p>
      <p>We work to introduce, improve and develop methods to support the quality of the service we deliver;</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Training and development of staff to be able to apply and deliver high standards of animal care.</li>
        <li>
          Continual development of knowledge to maintain an up to date delivery of health and
          welfare through use of close contact with Veterinary Practices Locally, Membership of
          Trade Associations, Connections with local Animal College and appropriate magazines and
          press.
        </li>
        <li>Application of knowledge through development and delivery of methods of work.</li>
        <li>The correct collection, recording and application of client’s instructions regarding the pets in our care.</li>
        <li>
          The correct explanation of our requirements (e.g. vaccinations, prices, opening times) in
          a friendly and knowledgeable manner.
        </li>
        <li>
          Continuous Improvement by a review of when things go wrong/ near miss in order to avoid
          re-occurrence of errors.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We aim to achieve this with the direct involvement and support of our employees and
        contractors. This is done through development of an annual strategy and regular
        communication of progress and results.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-2xl bg-cream-100 p-6 shadow-[var(--shadow-lift)]">
        <p class="!mt-0 font-bold text-moss-800">Looking for the Dog Grooming terms and conditions?</p>
        <p class="!mt-3">
          <a href="https://fairytailsdoggrooming.co.uk/terms-and-conditions/" class="btn btn-moss !no-underline">
            Grooming terms and conditions <span class="btn-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2>Our dog care policy</h2>
      <p><strong>DOG DAYCARE</strong></p>
      <p><strong>TERMS &amp; CONDITIONS (the Agreement)</strong></p>

      <p>1 By:</p>
      <p>a. enrolling a dog with The Fairy Tails,</p>
      <p>b. permitting a dog to attend The Fairy Tails, or</p>
      <p>
        c. accepting the services of The Fairy Tails Dog Day-care and its staff. The client is
        deemed to have accepted these Terms and Conditions
      </p>
      <p>
        2. The Fairy Tails may act in the client's absence as guardian of their dog and may perform
        or take any action which The Fairy Tails deem necessary in order to protect and keep in
        good health the client's dog.
      </p>

      <h3>Limitation of liability: the client's attention is particularly drawn to this clause</h3>
      <p>3. Client's Responsibility for Costs:</p>
      <p>
        The Client shall assume all financial responsibility for expenses incurred, whether by a
        veterinarian or any other party, arising from any injury, accident, or illness caused to or
        by their dog. The Client agrees to promptly cover such costs and expenses upon request.
      </p>
      <p>3.1. Fairy Tales' Liability Exemptions:</p>
      <p>The Agreement shall not restrict or disclaim Fairy Tales' liability for the following:</p>
      <p>
        a. Any instances of death or personal injury to a human being resulting from its
        negligence, the negligence of its employees, agents, or subcontractors.
      </p>
      <p>b. Cases involving fraud or fraudulent misrepresentation.</p>
      <p>
        c. Violations of the terms implied by section 2 of the Supply of Goods and Services Act
        1982 (pertaining to title and quiet possession), or any other liabilities that are
        non-restrictive or non-excludable under applicable law.
      </p>
      <p>
        3.2. Subject to clause 3.3, The Fairy Tails shall not be liable to the Client, whether in
        Agreement, tort (including negligence), breach of statutory duty, or otherwise, arising
        under or in connection with the Agreement for:
      </p>
      <p>a. Loss of profit,</p>
      <p>b. Loss of sales or business;</p>
      <p>C. Loss of agreements;</p>
      <p>d. Loss of anticipated savings; e Loss or damage to good will, and</p>
      <p>f. Any indirect or consequential loss.</p>
      <p>3.3. Limitation of Fairy Tails' Liability:</p>
      <p>
        Fairy Tails' overall liability to the Client, whether arising from the Agreement, tort
        (including negligence), violation of statutory obligations, or any other cause related to
        the Agreement, shall be capped at either £1,000 or the total fees paid under the Agreement,
        whichever amount is lower.
      </p>
      <p>3.4. Exclusion of Implied Terms under the Supply of Goods and Services Act 1982:</p>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent allowable by law, the Agreement excludes the terms implied by
        sections 3 to 5 of the Supply of Goods and Services Act 1982.
      </p>
      <p>3.5. Insurance Responsibilities:</p>
      <p>
        By accepting the figure outlined in clause 3.3 above and to facilitate the provisions
        specified in clause 5 below, the Client affirms their ability to obtain insurance coverage
        for their dog through a pet insurance policy, as well as the ability to insure their home
        and property contents through a house and contents insurance policy. It is advisable for
        the Client to inform their insurance providers about the day-care arrangement to ensure
        coverage under the relevant insurance policies. The Client acknowledges that The Fairy
        Tails can offer its competitive fees contingent on clients appropriately insuring their
        pets.
      </p>
      <p>3.6. The entirety of clause 3 shall survive termination of the Agreement.</p>

      <p>4. Transporting dogs</p>
      <p>
        The client's dog may be transported with other dogs in a Fairy Tails vehicle. The client
        agrees that The Fairy Tails cannot be held liable for death or injury to their dog in the
        event of a motor vehicle accident.
      </p>
      <p>5. Key Possession and Insurance Responsibility:</p>
      <p>
        The Fairy Tales may retain possession of the keys to the client's home, and it is the
        Client's responsibility to make the necessary arrangements with their own insurers in this
        regard.
      </p>
      <p>6. Client's Confirmation and Disclosure:</p>
      <p>
        The Client has expressly affirmed that their dog exhibits no history of aggressive or
        antisocial behaviour and has provided a complete and transparent disclosure of any traits
        or characteristics that might render their dog unsuitable for interaction with other dogs.
      </p>
      <p>7. Right to Cancel Due to Unsuitability:</p>
      <p>
        If The Fairy Tails determines that the client's dog is not suitable for our services, we
        retain the right to terminate the booking indefinitely, with immediate effect.
      </p>
      <p>8. Client's Obligation for Dog's Health:</p>
      <p>
        The Client commits to maintaining their dog's health by ensuring that all vaccinations,
        deworming, and flea prevention are kept current.
      </p>
      <p>9. Exemption from Liability for Pre-existing Conditions:</p>
      <p>
        The Client acknowledges and accepts that The Fairy Tails cannot be held responsible for any
        injuries resulting from pre-existing conditions of the dog or any inherent fragility,
        weakness, or breed-specific predispositions.
      </p>
      <p>10. Acknowledgment of Risks Associated with Animal Environments:</p>
      <p>
        The Client acknowledges and explicitly recognises that environments involving live animals
        inherently carry risks of injury or illness. The Client understands and willingly assumes
        the inherent risks and potential dangers associated with The Fairy Tales, including dog
        boarding and dog walking, encompassing but not limited to injuries or illnesses arising
        from dog altercations, vigorous play, pathogens, and natural disasters.
      </p>
      <p>11. Closure on Bank Holidays and the Holiday Season:</p>
      <p>
        The Fairy Tails will be closed on bank holidays and during the period between Christmas and
        New Year. Refunds or replacement days cannot be requested for any daycare services provided
        during these periods.
      </p>
      <p>12. Consent for Dog's Image Usage:</p>
      <p>
        The Client grants permission for their dog's image to be utilised in photographic or video
        formats for promotional material, social media, or any other format that The Fairy Tails
        deems suitable.
      </p>

      <h3>Opening hours</h3>
      <p>
        13. The normal opening hours of The Fairy Tails is from 8am to 5.30pm Monday to Friday,
        excluding Bank Holidays and Public Holidays.
      </p>
      <p>14. The provision of services outside of normal opening hours will be by prior arrangement only.</p>

      <h3>Fees</h3>
      <p>
        15. Fees for services are as displayed at The Fairy Tales
        <a href="/">www.thefairytails.co.uk</a> and may be revised at any time.
      </p>
      <p>
        16. Fees for services provided outside of normal opening hours will be as agreed in advance
        between The Fairy Tails and the client
      </p>
      <p>17. The client is responsible for ensuring that his/her dog is collected within normal opening hours.</p>
      <p>
        18. In the event that the client's dog is not collected during normal opening hours, the
        provisions of clause 20 will apply and a Late Collection Fee of £5 will be incurred by the
        client for every 30 minutes, or part thereof, within which the dog has not been collected.
      </p>
      <p>19. All fees are payable by the client on the day the service is provided by The Fairy Tails.</p>
      <p>
        Daycare. Late payment of fees may result in an administration charge of £25 and may be
        subject to an additional interest charge on the outstanding amount equivalent to 5% above
        the Bank of England Base Rate.
      </p>

      <h3>Collected dogs</h3>
      <p>
        20. In the event that the client's dog is not collected during normal opening hours, the
        provisions of Clause 18 above and Clauses 21 to 23 shall apply
      </p>
      <p>
        21. the Fairy Tails will attempt to contact the client by telephone using the telephone
        number(s) provided by the client.
      </p>
      <p>
        22. If the client cannot be contacted and/or the client's dog has not been collected within
        one hour of the end of normal opening hours, The Fairy Tails may, at its discretion, take
        any of the following steps:
      </p>
      <p>
        a. Arrange to relocate the client's dog to overnight accommodation in the care of The Fairy
        Tails;
      </p>
      <p>
        23. In the event that any of the steps set out in Clause 22 are taken, the client hereby
        accepts responsibility for the resulting fees of The Fairy Tails and any third party,
        including, but not limited to, fees for transportation, accommodation and food.
      </p>

      <h3>Force majeure</h3>
      <p>
        24. Neither party shall be in breach of this Agreement nor liable for delay in performing,
        or failure to perform, any of its obligations under this Agreement if such delay or failure
        result from events, circumstances or causes beyond its reasonable control.
      </p>

      <h3>Entire agreement</h3>
      <p>
        25. This agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties and supersedes and
        extinguishes all previous agreements, promises, assurances, warranties, representations,
        and understandings between them, whether written or oral, relating to its subject matter.
      </p>
      <p>
        26. Each party agrees that it shall have no remedies in respect of any statement,
        representation, assurances or warranty (whether made innocently or negligently) that is not
        set out in this agreement. Each party agrees that it shall have no claim for innocent or
        negligent misrepresentation or negligent misstatement based on any statement in this
        agreement.
      </p>

      <h3>Variation</h3>
      <p>
        27. No variation of the Agreement shall be effective unless it is in writing and notified
        to, or accepted by, The Fairy Tails Dog Daycare or its appointed director(s).
      </p>

      <h3>Waiver</h3>
      <p>
        28. A waiver of any right or remedy is only effective if given in writing and shall not be
        deemed a waiver of any subsequent breach or default. A delay or failure to exercise, or the
        single, or partial exercise of, any right or remedy shall not:
      </p>
      <p>a. waive that or any other right or remedy, or</p>
      <p>b. prevent or restrict the further exercise of that or any other right or remedy.</p>

      <h3>Severance</h3>
      <p>
        29. If any provision or part-provision of the Agreement is or becomes invalid, illegal or
        unenforceable and if modification is not possible, the relevant provision or part-provision
        shall be deemed deleted. Any modification to, or deletion of, a provision or part-
        provision under this clause shall not affect the validity and enforceability of the rest of
        the Agreement
      </p>

      <h3>Notices</h3>
      <p>
        30. Any notice or other communication given to a party under or in connection with the
        Agreement shall be in writing, addressed to that party at its registered office or such
        other address as that party may have specified to the other part in writing in accordance
        with this clause, and shall be delivered personally, or sent by pre-paid first class post
        or other next working day delivery service, commercial courier, fax or email to the correct
        email address if sent delivered-read (so email delivery and receipt can be acknowledged).
      </p>
      <p>31. A notice or other communication shall be deemed to have been received if:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>delivered personally, when left at the address provided by the client;</li>
        <li>
          sent by pre-paid first class post or other next working day delivery service to the same
          address, at 9.00 am on the second business day after posting;
        </li>
        <li>delivered by commercial courier, on the date and at the time that the courier's delivery receipt is signed; or</li>
        <li>sent by fax or email one business day after transmission.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        32. The provisions of clause 31 shall not apply to the service of any proceedings or other
        documents in any legal action.
      </p>

      <h3>Third parties</h3>
      <p>33. No one other than a party to the Agreement shall have any right to enforce any of its terms.</p>

      <h3>Interpretation</h3>
      <p>34. Within the Agreement</p>
      <p>a. words importing the masculine gender include the feminine;</p>
      <p>b. words importing the feminine gender include the masculine; and</p>
      <p>c. words in the singular include the plural and words in the plural include the singular</p>

      <h3>Governing law &amp; jurisdiction</h3>
      <p>
        35.The Agreement, and any dispute or claim (including non-Agreementual disputes or claims)
        arising out of, or in connection with, the Agreement or its subject matter or formation
        shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the law of England and Wales.
      </p>
      <p>
        36. Each party irrevocably agrees that the courts of England and Wales shall have exclusive
        jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim (including non-Agreement disputes or claims)
        arising out of or in connection with the Agreement or its subject matter or formation.
      </p>

      <h2>Why sometimes training a dog takes time at The Fairy Tails</h2>
      <p>
        There are different stages of behaviour development and they cannot be forced upon a dog.
        They must be developed.
      </p>
      <h3>Stages of learning and behaviour development in a dog:</h3>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2">
        {
          stages.map((stage, i) => (
            <div class="rounded-2xl border-2 border-cream-200 bg-cream-50 p-6">
              <p class="!mt-0 font-display text-4xl font-bold leading-none text-honey-400/80">{i + 1}</p>
              <p class="!mt-3 font-display text-lg font-bold text-moss-800">{stage.name}</p>
              <ul class="!mt-3 !space-y-2 text-sm">
                {stage.points.map((point) => (
                  <li>{point}</li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
      <p>
        We deal with complex cases, such as section 3 cases, therefore we ask you to please stay
        calm, patient and cool headed if a particular member of staff is not available to deal with
        your enquiry, as they may be dealing with a dog they cannot leave. However, we are always
        only one email away to answer any of your queries.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href={`mailto:${business.emails.info}`}>{business.emails.info}</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
